tomcat-multiple-server-client
=========

Pack of bash scripts to install on Cpanel's Easy Apache multiple tomcat servers.


=====================================================================

1.- USE

Before using this script, install on EasyApache's cPanel tomcat and allow user to use Apache Tomcat servlets. 
This scripts works thogeder with the default EasyApache installation, modifying the configuration files generated by cPanel.


	tomcat_setup.sh
		
		The script installs an Apache Tomcat server for one system user. Script need the following parameters:
		
		./tomcat_setup.sh <user> <user_domain> <tomcat_choice> <jdk_choice> <user_mem>
		
		To know which version of Apache Tomcat or JDK install, refer on the next chapter.
		
	tomcat_setup_interactive.sh
		
		This script allows to sysadmin to install step by step.
			
	tomcat_remove.sh
	
		This script has the operations to remove or reinstall an Apache Tomcat server from one user.

=====================================================================

2.- LIST OF APACHE TOMCAT SERVER AND JDK


		LIST OF APACHE TOMCAT SERVER VERSIONS:
			1. Tomcat 7.0.30
			2. Tomcat 7.0.29
			3. Tomcat 6.0.35
			4. Tomcat 5.5.35
		
		LIST OF JDK VERSIONS:
			1. JDK 7 x64
			2. JDK 6 x64
			3. JDK 5 i586
			4. <not_specified>

